Then, a quantum probability space can be defined as a quantum event space
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\events$
\end_inset

 together with a quantum probability measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\colon\events\rightarrow\left[0,1\right]$
