\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "10.2307/2308516,gleason1957,Redhead1987-REDINA,Maassen2010,Abramsky2012"
literal "true"

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\mu\left(\mathbb{0}\right) & =0\,, & \mu\left(\mathbb{1}\right) & =1\,, & \mu\left(\mathbb{1}-P\right) & =1-\mu\left(P\right)\,,\label{eq:QuantumProbability}
\end{align}

\end_inset

and for each pair of orthogonal projectors 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{0}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{1}$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mu\left(P_{0}+P_{1}\right)=\mu\left(P_{0}\right)+\mu\left(P_{1}\right)\,.\label{eq:QuantumProbability-Addition}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Because 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 respects the probability of events, if we restrict the domain of 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 on a classical event space 
\begin_inset Formula $2^{\Omega}$
\end_inset

