\begin_inset Formula $\varphi^{*}\mu\colon2^{\Omega}\rightarrow\left[0,1\right]$
\end_inset

 defined by precomposition 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left(\varphi^{*}\mu\right)\left(E\right)=\mu\left(\varphi\left(E\right)\right)\label{eq:classical-pullback}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

is a classical 
\family roman
\size normal
probability measure and called the pullback of 
\family default
\size default

\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon2^{\Omega}\rightarrow\events$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given a Hilbert space 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}$
\end_inset

 of dimension 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 and a probability assignment for every projector 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

, we can define the expectation value of an observable
\begin_inset space ~
